# ---- AMBIGUOUS (question itself is underspecified) ----
{"id": "ambiguous-001", "question": "How do I scale?", "golden_answer": "The question is ambiguous — Kubernetes supports scaling at multiple levels: scaling Pods within a Deployment (kubectl scale or HorizontalPodAutoscaler), scaling nodes via the Cluster Autoscaler, or scaling individual container resources via VerticalPodAutoscaler. The system should ask which kind of scaling is intended before answering.", "expected_source_files": [], "type": "ambiguous"}
{"id": "ambiguous-002", "question": "What's the best way to deploy?", "golden_answer": "The question is ambiguous — 'best' depends on context. For stateless apps, a Deployment is standard; for stateful workloads, a StatefulSet; for daemons that run on every node, a DaemonSet; for one-off batch work, a Job or CronJob. The system should ask what kind of workload before recommending an approach.", "expected_source_files": [], "type": "ambiguous"}
{"id": "ambiguous-003", "question": "How do I make my cluster faster?", "golden_answer": "The question is ambiguous — 'faster' could refer to API server latency, scheduling throughput, network throughput, application response time, or build/deploy turnaround. Each has different optimization techniques. The system should ask which dimension of performance is the concern.", "expected_source_files": [], "type": "ambiguous"}
